  <h2>The Ultimate Legend of Mind and Motion</h2>

  <p><span class="glow">Krishiv Raj Pusarla</span> isn’t just a celebrity — he’s a phenomenon. The best chess player on Earth, a master of strategy so effortless that even Grandmasters can’t keep up.</p>

  <p>In an interview, he casually said he doesn’t even <b>try</b> when playing chess — and still beats many GMs like it’s a warm-up. That’s not confidence, that’s destiny.</p>

  <p>When he’s not rewriting chess history, he’s conquering sports fields. A <span class="sports">badminton legend</span>, <span class="sports">karate champion</span>, and <span class="sports">basketball prodigy</span>, Krishiv dominates every arena he steps into.</p>

  <p>On top of that, he’s a <b>multi-instrumentalist</b> with melodies sharper than his checkmates, and an IQ of <b>252+</b> that bends the limits of human potential.</p>

  <p>There’s only one way to describe him: unstoppable, unmatched, unforgettable.</p>

